(6, 'Charlotte', 'coach', 'Perrottey', '2022-07-20 13:19:47', '2023-03-07 07:25:23', NULL, 'she/her', '', 'United States', 'a:2:{i:0;s:7:\"English\";i:1;s:6:\"French\";}', '54,67,62,49,63,64', '45,38,39', '15+ years of professional experience in the contemporary art world, working at Christie\'s auction house and the art advisories Allan Schwartzman, Inc. and Art Agency, Partners. Co-founder of Art to Zero, a NYC-based initiative dedicated to accelerating the visual arts\' transition to a decarbonized future, and member organization of PACT (Partners for Arts Climate Targets). Earned an MBA in Sustainability from Bard College.', 'Charlotte Perrottey', 'https://kiportdev.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/ultimatemember/336/profile_photo-190x190.jpg?1678173923', '', '336', 'approved'),
(7, 'Lia', 'coach', 'Colabello', '2022-07-20 13:19:47', '2023-03-07 07:25:23', NULL, 'she/her', '', 'United States', 'a:2:{i:0;s:7:\"English\";i:1;s:7:\"Spanish\";}', '54,67,58,49,68,52,64,66', '45,36,111,38,42,110', 'Lia Colabello develops and manages award-winning sustainability initiatives for organizations, with a focus on reducing single-use plastic, pursuing Climate Neutral and B Corporation certifications, implementing circular economy strategies and engaging entire brand ecosystems in these efforts. She is the Managing Principal of Planet+Purpose Solutions (PPS), a women-led, B Corp Certified boutique consulting practice whose impact is felt globally and spans an immense variety of organizations and industries. By launching organizational sustainability strategies, pursuing third-party certifications, establishing product and packaging stewardship initiatives, building sustainable corporate ethos through employee engagement and aligning clients with cause partners, Lia and her team accelerate solutions to some of the worlds greatest environmental challenges.\r\n\r\nLia was inspired by the power of the intersection of brands and purpose after working around the world with international sports organizations including the PGA TOUR and World Surf League, and later with ocean conservation organizations including the Surfrider Foundation and the 5 Gyres Institute to address the rise of plastic pollution. Originally from the North Shore of Oahu in Hawaii, Lia attended the University of Southern California, where she played varsity water polo and graduated with degrees in Broadcast Journalism and Anthropology. She has an MBA from Thunderbird School of Global Management at Arizona State University. Lia lives in Charleston, South Carolina, and loves to explore the ocean and waterways around the Lowcountry with her family.', 'Lia Colabello', 'https://kiportdev.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/ultimatemember/335/profile_photo-190x190.png?1678173923', '', '335', 'approved'),
(8, 'Marie-Claude', 'coach', 'Mongeon', '2022-07-20 13:19:47', '2023-03-07 07:25:23', NULL, 'She/her/elle', '', 'Canada', 'a:3:{i:0;s:7:\"English\";i:1;s:6:\"French\";i:2;s:7:\"Spanish\";}', '56,61,55,58,49', '45,36,38,42,39', 'Marie-Claude Mongeon currently works at the Muse dart contemporain de Montral.  She previously held various positions at the National Gallery of Canada for over 15 years, where she recently led an ongoing discussion group on greening museum activities. She holds two Bachelors degrees from the University of Ottawa, in visual arts and art history, as well as an International Baccalaureate Diploma in natural sciences.  She is currently pursuing a graduate\'s degree in Corporate Sustainability and Social Responsibility at St. Mike\'s University at the University of Toronto and a degree in gestion et dveloppement durable at HC Montral.', 'Marie-Claude Mongeon', 'https://kiportdev.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/ultimatemember/266/profile_photo-190x190.jpg?1678173923', '', '266', 'approved'),
(9, 'Ekaterina', 'coach', 'Egorova', '2022-07-20 13:19:47', '2023-03-07 07:25:23', NULL, '', '', 'Russian Federation', 'a:3:{i:0;s:7:\"English\";i:1;s:7:\"Russian\";i:2;s:7:\"Spanish\";}', '', '', 'Founder of Moscow Circular. Circular economy expert.\r\n\r\nEx-partner of the first zero waste shop in Moscow and sustainability agency. Guide of Food System Vision Prize organized by OpenIDEO, Second Muse and the Rockefeller Foundation. OpenIDEO Moscow Chapter organizer. Pioneer and mentor of the Circulareconomy program by Ellen MacArthur Foundation From Linear to Circular. Insummer of 2020, she founded the Moscow Circular a project, which helps businesses, cities and territories in Russia to switch to a circular economy.', 'Ekaterina Egorova', 'https://kiportdev.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/ultimatemember/139/profile_photo-190x190.jpg?1678173923', '', '139', 'approved'),
