(12, 'Alice', 'coach', 'Bonnot', '2022-07-20 13:19:47', '2023-03-07 07:25:23', NULL, 'She/Her', '', 'United Kingdom', 'a:2:{i:0;s:7:\"English\";i:1;s:6:\"French\";}', '67,70,61,58,49,68,65,71,66', '45,36,37,38,41,42,110,40,39', 'Alice Bonnot (she/her) is an independent art curator, sustainability consultant, writer and speaker interested in the development of environmentally sustainable curatorial and artistic practices with a drive towards eco solutions. She is the founding director of villa villa, a sustainable and climate-conscious arts programme dedicated to supporting contemporary artists, curators, writers, thinkers, and other cultural and environmental practitioners committed to more ecologically sensitive practices.\r\n\r\nAs a curator, Alice focuses on developing environmentally respectful exhibitions that address socio-political and environmental issues, as well as broader concerns relating to society. Her current research deals with subjects such as deep ecology, intersectional environmentalism and ecofeminisms. She teaches the course Curating an ecologically sensitive exhibition and is regularly invited to speak about art and ecology. \r\n\r\nAs a sustainability consultant, Alice helps cultural institutions embrace the challenges and opportunities associated with the adoption of sustainable working methods. She worked as an advisor on the development of the upcoming \'Exhibition Ki Book\'. Her writing appears regularly in art publications, including Umbigo Magazine, for which she writes as a recurring contributor. She is part of the Green Art Lab Alliance\'s working group on Future Materials.\r\n\r\n>> When she is not working, you can find her connecting with more-than-human beings in nature or embracing the liquid dimensions of her \'ecological self\' while surfing in the oceanic currents.', 'Alice Bonnot', 'https://kiportdev.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/ultimatemember/68/profile_photo-190x190.jpg?1678173923', '', '68', 'approved'),
(13, 'Christopher', 'coach', 'Garthe', '2022-07-20 13:19:47', '2023-03-07 07:25:23', NULL, '', 'Berlin', 'Germany', '', '', '', '', 'Christopher Garthe', 'https://kiportdev.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/ultimatemember/57/profile_photo-190x190.jpg?1678173923', '', '57', 'approved'),
(14, 'Thierry', 'coach', 'Leonardi', '2022-07-20 13:19:47', '2023-03-07 07:25:23', NULL, '', '', 'France', '', '', '', '', 'Thierry Leonardi', 'https://kiportdev.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/ultimatemember/51/profile_photo-190x190.jpg?1678173923', '', '51', 'approved'),
(15, 'Douglas', 'coach', 'Worts', '2022-07-20 13:19:47', '2023-03-07 07:25:23', NULL, 'He/Him/His', '', 'Canada', 'a:1:{i:0;s:7:\"English\";}', '54,67,70,61,55,58,51,62,49,59,63,57,60,50,71,52', '43,45,36,46,42', 'I\'ve been a museum professional for over 40 years. My experience, (primarily at the Art Gallery of Ontario, in Toronto, Canada), focused on experimental exhibit development in an art museum setting, as well as on audience research. I was one of the founding directors of the Visitor-Studies Association. One of my most interesting areas of research has been in \'visitor-based creativity\' - specifically creativity generated by visitors as they engage with artworks. \r\n\r\nFor the past 25 years, my research, publishing and teaching has been focused on the potential of museums to play a meaningful role in fostering cultural adaptation and change in a fast-transforming world. Central to this work has been the need to embrace something called \"systems thinking\" - which involves understanding how multiple, interdependent systems function together in dynamic balance. For museums to become catalysts of cultural adaptation, it is important to be able to use systems thinking to understand current trends and to generate effective, innovative interventions in the living culture.', 'Douglas Worts', 'https://kiportdev.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/ultimatemember/45/profile_photo-190x190.jpeg?1678173923', '', '45', 'approved'),
(16, 'Kim', 'coach', 'Kraczon', '2022-07-20 13:19:47', '2023-03-07 07:25:23', NULL, 'she/her', '', 'Netherlands', 'a:2:{i:0;s:7:\"English\";i:1;s:6:\"German\";}', '67,49,68,65,64,69,66', '47,45,36,111,38,41,39', 'After finishing a second bachelors degree in the Conservation of Modern Materials and Technical Cultural Heritage at the Hochschule fr Technik und Wirtschaft in Berlin, I worked for 8 years as the resident conservator at Studio Olafur Eliasson in Berlin, Germany where I was responsible for repairs and conservation treatments of artworks, as well as developing sustainable strategies for art production and packing systems. Im currently pursuing my masters degree in the Conservation and Restoration of Contemporary Art at the University of Amsterdam, where I intend to focus on the use of recycled materials and emerging bioplastics and biomaterials in contemporary art. Aside from my role as a Ki Coach in Ki Culture, I also serve as the Director of Materials and am at the helm of the Materials Ki Book. I additionally lead Gallery Climate Coalitions Packaging and Materials Research Committee and am one of the founding members of the Berlin branch of the Gallery Climate Coalition.', 'Kim Kraczon', 'https://kiportdev.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/ultimatemember/33/profile_photo-190x190.jpg?1678173923', '', '33', 'approved'),
(17, 'Nicole', 'coach', 'Smith', '2022-07-20 13:19:47', '2023-03-07 07:25:23', NULL, 'she/her', '', 'United States', 'a:1:{i:0;s:7:\"English\";}', '56,70,61,58,51,49,59,65,60,50,52', '45,36,38,42,39', 'Nicole has spent her career as a driving force for positive change in diversity, equity, accessibility and inclusion at museums with the principal belief that museums should be for everyone. Through over 15 years of  museum experience, Nicole has advocated for this belief in her work with visitor experience, membership, communications, programming and most importantly sustainability and accessibility. \r\n\r\nThrough her work, Nicole has helped museums navigate diversity, equity accessibility  and inclusion work. Her efforts have been recognized with institutional awards at the local and national level. In 2017, Nicole was recognized as an Emerging Leader for Arts and Disability by  the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. \r\n\r\nNicole continues to serve and advocate through her current roles including: As the founder of Before Thought  where she provides consulting services that focuses on inclusive accessibility practices for people with disabilities in the cultural sector. And as the Co-Director of Social Sustainability at Ki Culture, a non-profit that advocates for museums as spaces that benefit people, places and the planet.', 'Nicole Smith', 'https://kiportdev.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/ultimatemember/14/profile_photo-190x190.jpg?1678173923', '', '14', 'approved'),
